{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:proverbs.5",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 5,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 5 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:1",
      "text": "My son, attend unto my wisdom, and bow thine ear to my understanding:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:2",
      "text": "That thou mayest regard discretion, and that thy lips may keep knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:3",
      "text": "For the lips of a strange woman drop as an honeycomb, and her mouth is smoother than oil:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:4",
      "text": "But her end is bitter as wormwood, sharp as a twoedged sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:5",
      "text": "Her feet go down to death; her steps take hold on hell.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:6",
      "text": "Lest thou shouldest ponder the path of life, her ways are moveable, that thou canst not know them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:7",
      "text": "Hear me now therefore, O ye children, and depart not from the words of my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:8",
      "text": "Remove thy way far from her, and come not nigh the door of her house:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:9",
      "text": "Lest thou give thine honour unto others, and thy years unto the cruel:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:10",
      "text": "Lest strangers be filled with thy wealth; and thy labours be in the house of a stranger;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:11",
      "text": "And thou mourn at the last, when thy flesh and thy body are consumed,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:12",
      "text": "And say, How have I hated instruction, and my heart despised reproof;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:13",
      "text": "And have not obeyed the voice of my teachers, nor inclined mine ear to them that instructed me!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:14",
      "text": "I was almost in all evil in the midst of the congregation and assembly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:15",
      "text": "Drink waters out of thine own cistern, and running waters out of thine own well.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:16",
      "text": "Let thy fountains be dispersed abroad, and rivers of waters in the streets.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:17",
      "text": "Let them be only thine own, and not strangers’ with thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:18",
      "text": "Let thy fountain be blessed: and rejoice with the wife of thy youth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:19",
      "text": "Let her be as the loving hind and pleasant roe; let her breasts satisfy thee at all times; and be thou ravished always with her love.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:20",
      "text": "And why wilt thou, my son, be ravished with a strange woman, and embrace the bosom of a stranger?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:21",
      "text": "For the ways of man are before the eyes of the Lord, and he pondereth all his goings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:22",
      "text": "His own iniquities shall take the wicked himself, and he shall be holden with the cords of his sins.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.5.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:23",
      "text": "He shall die without instruction; and in the greatness of his folly he shall go astray.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
